Availability:Public
Title:Scene Fringe
Crumbs: %ROOT%, Engine, Engine/Rendering/PostProcessEffects
Description:Chromatic aberration effect that simulates the color shifts near the edges of real-world camera lenses.

[EXCERPT:SceneFringe_Desc]
**Scene Fringe** is a chromatic aberration effect that simulates the color shifts in real-world camera lenses. The effect is mostly noticeable near the edges of the image.
[/EXCERPT:SceneFringe_Desc]

[REGION:imagetable]
| ![Without Scene Fringe](scenefringe_0.png)(w:455) | ![With Scene Fringe](scenefringe_2.png)(w:455) |
| :----: | :----: |
| Without Scene Fringe | With Scene Fringe (extreme settings) |
[/REGION]


| Property | Description |
| -------- | ----------- |
| **Fringe Intensity** | A scaling factor that controls how much shifting occurs. [INCLUDE:#Intensity] |
| **Fringe Saturation** | A scaling factor that controls the saturation of the shifted colors. Lower values produce a more blurred result, while higher values make the color shifting much more pronounced. |

